<AbstractNarration>0079196&lt;br/&gt;Majda&lt;br/&gt;This Major Research Instrumentation award to Courant Institute of New York University provides a clustered workstation environment for research and education related to evaluation and testing of General Circulation Models, and their application to climate problems. The computer system will be part of a new program in Atmosphere-Ocean Sciences at the institute.  The project is supported by the Division of Ocean Sciences at NSF. New York University will provide cost-share support for 30% of total project costs.&lt;br/&gt;***&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
